INLINE TAGS

<b></b>                     - bold
<i></i>                     - italize
<sub></sub>                 - subscript
<sup></sup>                 - supscript
<pre></pre>                 - preformatted text
<q></q>                     - if you're just quoting a short phrase in the middle of your sentence

<abbr></abbr>               - abbreviations
<cite></cite>               - citations, used to include a reference
<del></del>                 - indicate deleted text, opposite of <ins> tag
<dfn></dfn>                 - definition
<ins></ins>                 - inserted text, opposite of <del> tag


BLOCK TAGS

<blockquote></blcokquote>   - if you're quoting a paragraph or more of text
<code></code>               - used to insert programming code
<p></p>                     - create a paragraph
<ul></ul>                   - unordered list
<ol></ol>                   - ordered list

